h3. Summary
In JIRA Service Desk, when searching from the Help Center, provided suggestions redirect to the Application Links' "Application URL" when clicking documents from Confluence, whereas, using the similar search box from within a specific Service Desk properly uses the "Display URL".

h3. Environment
* JIRA 6.4.6, 6.4.7
* Confluence 5.8.5, 5.8.14
* Service Desk 2.5.0, 2.5.2

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Setup *JIRA* with *JIRA Service Desk* and *Confluence* on any of the above versions;
# Create an [unproxied Application Link|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/KB/How+to+create+an+unproxied+Application+Link] between *JIRA* and *Confluence* (or any other approach that results in different addresses for *Application URL* and *Display URL*);
# Link a *Service Desk* in JIRA to a *Space* in Confluence to be used as a *Knowledge Base*, under the Service Desk's settings;
# Create one or more page/s within the linked Confluence Space;
# From within the *Help Center*, search for one of the created pages;
#* Notice the URL displayed is the *Application URL*. In some cases, the URL may only be accessible from within the internal network, causing the browser to display an empty window;
#* Another possible problem is running JIRA over HTTPS and having the *Application URL* setup as HTTP, which, even though customers may be able to reach the referred address, no modern browser will display the content due to the usage of an "insecure protocol" inside a "secure page";

h3. Expected Results
Both links from the *Help Center* and the *Customer Portal* should use the *Display URL* of the Confluence instance.

h3. Actual Results
The *Help Center* search box will use the *Application URL* instead of the *Display URL* for the linked Confluence instance, whereas the *Customer Portal* _for a specific Service Desk_ will properly use the *Display URL* of the linked Confluence when running searches through the search box.

h3. Workaround
Use the same address for both the *Display URL* and *Application URL*.

h3. Solution
Update *JIRA Service Desk* to any version later than 2.5.4.

