h3. Problem Definition

JIRA Service Desk currently pauses the SLA if arbitrary code is used to execute a custom event, for example a plugin fires one. This can be reproduced by using the Script Runner plugin and executing the below:

{code:java}
import com.atlassian.jira.ComponentManager
import com.atlassian.jira.event.issue.IssueEventDispatcher
import com.atlassian.jira.issue.IssueManager
import com.atlassian.jira.issue.Issue
import com.atlassian.jira.util.ImportUtils
ComponentManager componentManager = ComponentManager.getInstance()
def userManager = componentManager.getUserUtil()
def user = userManager.getUser("admin")
IssueManager issueManager = componentManager.getIssueManager()
Issue issue = issueManager.getIssueObject("DESK-1")
IssueEventDispatcher.dispatchEvent(10000, issue, user, null, null, null, null, true);
ImportUtils.setIndexIssues(true);
{code}

As a third-party plugin developer interacting with JIRA Service Desk issues I do not want the SLA to be changed if I'm sending a custom event.

h3. Suggested Solution

Only change SLA for system events.

